1ï¸âƒ£ Two Sum (Array)
ğŸ”¹ Problem

Given an array and a target, check if any two numbers sum to the target.

ğŸ§  Python Code (5 lines)
a=[2,7,11,15]; t=9
s=set()
for x in a:
    if t-x in s: print(True); break
    s.add(x)

ğŸ“– Explanation

We use a set to store numbers we have already seen.

For each number x, we check if target - x exists in the set.

If yes â†’ pair found.

If no â†’ store x and continue.

â±ï¸ Interview Insight

Time Complexity: O(n)

Space Complexity: O(n)

ğŸ¤ How to Explain in Interview

â€œI used hashing to reduce the time complexity from O(nÂ²) to O(n) by storing visited elements.â€

2ï¸âƒ£ Kadaneâ€™s Algorithm (Maximum Subarray Sum)
ğŸ”¹ Problem

Find the maximum sum of a contiguous subarray.

ğŸ§  Python Code (4 lines)
a=[-2,1,-3,4,-1,2,1]
s=m=a[0]
for x in a[1:]:
    s=max(x,s+x); m=max(m,s)
print(m)

ğŸ“– Explanation

s stores the current subarray sum.

At each element, we decide:

start new subarray (x)

or extend previous (s + x)

m keeps track of the maximum sum found so far.

â±ï¸ Interview Insight

Time Complexity: O(n)

Space Complexity: O(1)

ğŸ¤ How to Explain in Interview

â€œKadaneâ€™s algorithm uses dynamic programming to track the best subarray ending at each index.â€

ğŸ¤ FAANG Interview Round (Professional Answers)

Q1. Why is Two Sum important?
A: It tests hashing and optimization from brute force to linear time.

Q2. Can Two Sum be solved without extra space?
A: Yes, using sorting + two pointers, but hashing is faster.

Q3. What does Kadaneâ€™s algorithm solve?
A: Maximum sum contiguous subarray.

Q4. Why Kadane is O(n)?
A: Each element is processed exactly once.
